==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hybridizable
<hw>Hy"brid*i`za*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Capable of
forming a hybrid, or of being subjected to a hybridizing process;
capable of producing a hybrid by union with another species or
stock.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Hybridizable</qex> genera are rarer than is generally
supposed, even in gardens where they are so often operated upon, under
circumstances most favorable to the production of hybrids.</q>
<rj><qau>J. D. Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hybridization</ent>⟦br⟧
